Memory structure is same as JAVA a reference is in stack and real object lives in heap 
whenever reference is removed the object is deleted by garbage collector





PYTHON GARBAGE COLLECTION ->


PYTHON DOES NOT HAVE CONCURRENT GARBAGE COLLECTION !!

1. Reference Method-> Whenever any object is referenced the count of reference is increased conversely whenever that reference is removed count is decremented
as soon as count reaches to 0 object is instantly deleted

Limitation
There can be circular references which may prevent the python to go GC



2. Generational Garbage Collection -> Based on the idea young objects die fast


WeakRef doesnt increase the reference count

